{"id":171654,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canada_Border_Services_Agency","text":"The Canada Border Services Agency (CBSA) () is the Canadian government agency with a duty to act as border guards and customs services.\nThe agency was started on December 12, 2003 (the same day Paul Martin became Prime Minister of Canada), by an order-in-council joining Canada Customs with border and law enforcement agents from the Department of Citizenship and Immigration Canada (CIC) and the Canadian Food Inspection Agency (CFIA).","categories":[],"infobox_types":["Law enforcement agency"],"annotations":[{"uri":"Canada","surface_form":"Canadian","offset":51},{"uri":"Government","surface_form":"government","offset":60},{"uri":"Agency","surface_form":"agency","offset":71},{"uri":"Border_guard","surface_form":"border guard","offset":100},{"uri":"Customs","surface_form":"customs","offset":118},{"uri":"Paul_Martin","surface_form":"Paul Martin","offset":194},{"uri":"Prime_Minister_of_Canada","surface_form":"Prime Minister of Canada","offset":213},{"uri":"Order-in-council","surface_form":"order-in-council","offset":246},{"uri":"Canada_Customs","surface_form":"Canada Customs","offset":271},{"uri":"Law_enforcement","surface_form":"law enforcement","offset":302},{"uri":"Ministry_(government_department)","surface_form":"Department","offset":334},{"uri":"Citizenship_and_Immigration_Canada","surface_form":"Citizenship and Immigration Canada","offset":348},{"uri":"Canadian_Food_Inspection_Agency","surface_form":"Canadian Food Inspection Agency","offset":397}]}